The paper deals with algorithms for directed graphs and their connectivity properties, which are fundamental topics in computer science. The use of network coding and matrix multiplication suggests a connection to network information theory and numerical algorithms, respectively, which are covered by cs.NI and cs.NA. The combinatorial algorithms and lower bounds suggest a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), and game theory (cs.GT).
